# Git — Simplified

Git is a free tool that helps you **save versions of your project**, so you can go back if something breaks. Think of it like Google Docs version history—but for code and files.

## Why You Should Care

- It tracks your progress.
- It lets you undo mistakes.
- It helps you work with others without messing up each other’s work.

## How to Install Git

- **Windows:** Download it from [git-scm.com](https://git-scm.com/download/win) and follow the setup.
- **macOS:** Open Terminal and run:  
  `brew install git` *(requires Homebrew)*
- **Linux (Ubuntu):**  
  `sudo apt install git`

## Getting Started

After installing, try this in your terminal:

```bash
git --version
